President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Earl Robert Miller as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Peoples Republic of Bangladesh. Miller is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has been an American diplomat since 1987. He has served in various positions, including Ambassador to Botswana, Consul General in Johannesburg, and Regional Security Officer at several embassies. Miller also served in the United States Marine Corps and has received numerous awards for his service. Trump has also announced his intent to nominate Christopher P. Vincze as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation.